## Verification Checklist

### Settings behavior

- toggling a provider immediately reorders the Status Bar page
- disabled providers move below enabled providers
- disabling a provider removes it from multi-provider selection automatically
- re-enabling a provider restores it as a visible status bar candidate

### Status bar rendering

- disabled providers do not appear in the status bar output
- disabled providers do not appear in menu sections that should respect enabled state
- no stale provider remains selected after being disabled

### Subscription page

- enabled providers sort above disabled providers
- orphaned rows remain visible but clearly de-prioritized
- custom plan editing still persists correctly
- preset selection still persists correctly

### OpenCode family

- pay-as-you-go label matches the actual billed product
- OpenCode Go and Zen do not get merged into the wrong category
- no misleading `OpenCode Zen` label remains in pay-as-you-go if the data is actually for OpenCode pay-as-you-go

## Risks

- The current codebase appears to contain partially overlapping historical concepts for status bar modes.
- The OpenCode product family is not yet modeled clearly enough in the current provider/subscription architecture.
- A careless UI-only rename would hide the underlying modeling problem instead of fixing it.

## Open Questions For Implementation

These must be answered before the implementation phase finalizes the OpenCode-related changes:

- Does `OpenCodeZenProvider` fetch only Zen subscription data, or does it currently fetch OpenCode pay-as-you-go usage under a misleading identifier?
- Should `OpenCode Go` be represented as:
  - a new `ProviderIdentifier`
  - a subscription preset under an existing provider
  - or an account-level subscription variant under one provider family?
- Should `Zen` be represented as:
  - its own subscribable provider
  - or a plan/account subtype of the OpenCode family?

## Done Definition

This work is complete only when:

- the Status Bar settings page is simplified to the real product behavior
- provider visibility rules are consistent across settings and runtime rendering
- enabled-first sorting works on both Status Bar and Subscription pages
- Critical Badge is moved to General
- OpenCode / OpenCode Go / Zen are no longer conflated in the UI or data model